name: I Don't Feel At Home In This World Anymore
description:
Lately I have been feeling a disconnect with the world around me, even more than the usual amount. My mornings have become unbearable and the burden of living makes the act of waking up   quite a task. All the traumatic memories of my past seem to dance in a circle around me throughout the day and I constantly try to find some sense before I self destruct.

I wonder how do the people around me do this life thing? Maybe they have engaged themselves in a rewards program so that they always have something to look forward to, something to serve as a treat for being a good boy/girl. Maybe its a night out at the club on the weekend, a road trip or some time with friends and family that they look forward to. But me? I feel I have nothing to look forward to and I always ask myself, how the fxck did this happen?

Perhaps I took life for granted or the other way around and now I only find refuge in indifference. I feel like a stranger in my own body, burning in the flames of my apathy!
